sentences: Marisa Rezende (born 8 August 1944) is a Brazilian music educator and composer.
The couple moved in 1964 to Boston, Massachusetts, where her husband worked on a master's degree at MIT.
Rezende had two daughters in Boston, and when the family moved back to Rio in 1967, she had a third daughter before resuming her studies in composition.
In 1989 she helped to found Musica Nova, an organization to premiere new music compositions, working with Rodolfo Caesar and Rodrigo Cicchelli.
In 1999 she was awarded the Bolsa Vitae de Artes.
She retired from teaching in 2002 but operates the Music and Technology Lab at the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro and continues work as a composer.
